  "prompt": "Someone deleted me on snapchat, so I deleted him & now he appears in my Added me section, but I cannot see his score. Does this mean he added me back?",
  "response": "Yes, if someone appears in your \"Added Me\" section on Snapchat, it typically means that they have indeed added you back. However, if you cannot see their score, it may indicate that they haven't fully accepted your friend request yet or there's a glitch in the app. To confirm whether they've successfully added you back, try sending them a Snap or check your friend's list directly. If they appear there, you've been re-added as friends on the platform.",
